        "When `server_test.rb` is called from outside of its directory on a system that does not have the RethinkDB Ruby driver installed it fails with a message about `require` failing. The reason is the `require` statements are hard-coded for `pwd`, rather than being based on `__FILE__`.  As an example of the error:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngantz:build teapot$ ./test/rql_test/test-runner server_test.rb \r\nUsing rethinkdb binary from /Users/teapot/buildslave/test-osx/build/build/debug_clang_notcmalloc\r\n\r\n== Running server_test.rb test\r\n== Failed server_test.rb test with result code 1 (/Users/teapot/buildslave/test-osx/build/test/rql_test/server_test.rb.test) Output:\r\n/System/Library/Frameworks/Ruby.framework/Versions/2.0/usr/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require': cannot load such file -- rethinkdb (LoadError)\r\n\tfrom /System/Library/Frameworks/Ruby.framework/Versions/2.0/usr/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require'\r\n\tfrom /Users/teapot/buildslave/test-osx/build/test/rql_test/server_test.rb:5:in `<main>'\r\n\r\n\r\n== Failed 1 test (of 1) in 2.29 seconds!\r\n\tserver_test.rb\r\n```"
